In this memorandum, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. delegates authority to the Secretary of State to direct the drawdown of up to $2.85 billion in defense articles and services, as well as military education and training, to provide assistance to Ukraine. This delegation of authority is made under section 506(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. The Secretary of State is also tasked with making the necessary determinations required under this section to direct the drawdown. The memorandum concludes by authorizing the publication of this memorandum in the Federal Register.